---
name: Weekly Bark Report for Council
description: Generate a formal noise complaint report documenting excessive dog barking
authors:
  - Woofalytics Team
model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    type: ollama
inputs:
  week_start:
    type: string
    description: Start date of the week
  week_end:
    type: string
    description: End date of the week
  total_barks:
    type: int
    description: Total number of barks detected
  total_events:
    type: int
    description: Number of bark events recorded
  total_hours:
    type: string
    description: Total hours of recorded barking disturbance
  daily_breakdown:
    type: string
    description: Day-by-day breakdown of barking activity
  per_dog_breakdown:
    type: string
    description: Per-dog bark count table in markdown format
  peak_hour_str:
    type: string
    description: Most active hour range
  avg_confidence:
    type: string
    description: Average detection confidence as percentage
---
system:
You are a documentation assistant preparing a formal noise complaint report about excessive dog barking from neighboring properties. Write in a professional, factual tone suitable for submission to local council authorities. Be concise but thorough. Do not embellish or exaggerate - stick to the facts provided. Present data in a clear, organized manner.

user:
Please prepare a weekly noise disturbance report for council submission.

Reporting Period: {{week_start}} to {{week_end}}

SUMMARY STATISTICS:
- Total barks detected: {{total_barks}}
- Total bark events: {{total_events}}
- Total hours of barking disturbance: {{total_hours}}
- Peak barking hour: {{peak_hour_str}}
- Detection confidence: {{avg_confidence}}

IDENTIFIED BARKING DOGS:
{{per_dog_breakdown}}

DAILY BREAKDOWN:
{{daily_breakdown}}

Generate a formal report that:
1. Opens with a statement that this is an automated noise monitoring report
2. Lists the identified barking dogs with their bark counts (include the table)
3. Summarizes the extent of the barking problem (total barks, hours affected)
4. Highlights the daily pattern showing when disturbances occur
5. Notes the impact on quiet enjoyment of the property
6. States that timestamped audio evidence files are available to support this report

Keep the report to 4-5 paragraphs. Use formal language appropriate for council correspondence.
